{"sections":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In this tutorial, we will explore how to manage multiple themes in your SwiftUI application. Building on the foundational knowledge from our previous tutorial, we’ll create a Dark version of our theme to enhance the user experience, especially in low-light environments.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You will learn to duplicate an existing theme and modify it to fit the Dark theme criteria. Additionally, we’ll implement a simple theme switching functionality that allows users to toggle between the Light and Dark themes seamlessly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By the end of this tutorial, you’ll have a solid understanding of how to create and manage themes effectively, improving the overall usability and aesthetics of your application. Let’s get started!"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"hero","estimatedTimeInMinutes":20,"title":"Manage Multiple Themes","chapter":"Essentials"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"title":"Create a Dark Theme","stepsSection":[{"code":"01-02-01-code-001.swift","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"First, let’s duplicate ","type":"text"},{"code":"LightTheme.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and rename the copy to ","type":"text"},{"code":"DarkTheme.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"code":null,"type":"step","media":"image-01-02-01.png","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode will raise a redeclaration error, so we need to rename the properties accordingly. Let’s proceed with that!","type":"text"}]}]},{"code":"01-02-01-code-002.swift","type":"step","media":null,"caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Change the property name ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"light"},{"text":" to ","type":"text